Russian President Vladimir Putin has said North Korean leader Kim Jong-un needs international security guarantees if he is to end his nuclear programme. Such guarantees need to be offered within a multinational framework, he added, following talks near Vladivostok in Russia’s far east. Mr Kim praised the summit as a “very meaningful one-on-one exchange”. Mr Putin said North Korea’s leader was “fairly open”. Spurned by Washington, North Korea’s Kim seeks a friend in Putin Trump-Kim summit’s collapse exposes the risks of one-to-one diplomacy NORTH KOREA: Kim Jong-un leaves for Vietnam by train